WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.850 --> 00:00:14.550
Coraline Jones always dreamed of finding a better

2
00:00:14.550 --> 00:00:15.250
world.

3
00:00:25.460 --> 00:00:28.220
A world more exciting than this.

4
00:00:29.260 --> 00:00:32.400
But never did she imagine that she'd discover

5
00:00:32.400 --> 00:00:35.620
it in her own home.

6
00:00:42.260 --> 00:00:44.160
A parallel place.

7
00:00:44.360 --> 00:00:46.340
We've been waiting for you, Coraline.

8
00:00:46.820 --> 00:00:48.740
Where parents are always fun.

9
00:00:48.900 --> 00:00:50.340
I love your garden!

10
00:00:50.820 --> 00:00:52.260
I can't believe you did this.

11
00:00:52.700 --> 00:00:54.860
And everything is so good.

12
00:00:54.960 --> 00:00:56.720
Wow, let's shake him, baby.

13
00:00:57.220 --> 00:00:59.300
It just can't be real.

14
00:01:00.100 --> 00:01:02.720
Mom, you're just in time for supper, dear.

15
00:01:03.080 --> 00:01:04.360
You're not my mother.

16
00:01:05.140 --> 00:01:07.380
My mother doesn't have...

17
00:01:09.400 --> 00:01:09.940
Buttons?

18
00:01:10.160 --> 00:01:10.820
Do you like them?

19
00:01:11.420 --> 00:01:12.980
I'm your other mother, silly.

20
00:01:13.740 --> 00:01:15.720
You probably think this world is a dream

21
00:01:15.720 --> 00:01:16.500
come true.

22
00:01:17.220 --> 00:01:18.280
My name!

23
00:01:18.500 --> 00:01:19.500
But you're wrong.

24
00:01:20.180 --> 00:01:22.140
You do like it here, don't you, Coraline?

25
00:01:22.240 --> 00:01:23.580
You could stay here forever.

26
00:01:24.120 --> 00:01:26.240
There's one tiny little thing we need to

27
00:01:26.240 --> 00:01:26.460
do.

28
00:01:27.700 --> 00:01:28.880
Black is traditional.

29
00:01:30.260 --> 00:01:32.980
She's got this whole world where everything's better,

30
00:01:33.100 --> 00:01:34.800
but it's all a trap.

31
00:01:34.800 --> 00:01:37.360
You may come out when you've learned to

32
00:01:37.360 --> 00:01:38.680
be a loving daughter.

33
00:01:40.240 --> 00:01:42.640
From Henry Selick, the director of The Nightmare

34
00:01:42.640 --> 00:01:46.780
Before Christmas, comes a world of extraordinary imagination.

35
00:01:49.920 --> 00:01:50.920
Spooky secrets.

36
00:01:51.040 --> 00:01:51.720
Who are you?

37
00:01:51.880 --> 00:01:53.480
You're in terrible danger, Coral.

38
00:01:57.060 --> 00:01:58.740
And daring discoveries.

39
00:01:59.040 --> 00:02:01.480
I still have to find my parents to

40
00:02:01.480 --> 00:02:02.000
set them free.

41
00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:08.199
This year, when adventure comes knocking, there are

42
00:02:08.199 --> 00:02:12.260
some doors that should never be opened.

43
00:02:14.960 --> 00:02:16.680
I'm not scared!

44
00:02:19.960 --> 00:02:20.700
Coraline.

45
00:02:20.860 --> 00:02:22.680
Written for the screen and directed by Henry

46
00:02:22.680 --> 00:02:23.060
Selick.

47
00:02:23.300 --> 00:02:24.840
Presented in Real-D 3D.
